# Memento — Project Standards

## Architecture Principles
- **Feature-first**: code lives next to the feature it belongs to
- **Separation of concerns**: route → controller → service → repository (backend); page → feature → ui (frontend)
- **Single responsibility**: one reason to change per module
- **Shared API contract**: types in `shared/src/types/` are the single source of truth for all request/response shapes — never duplicate them

## Naming Conventions

| Thing | Pattern | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Files | `kebab-case` | `user-profile.ts` |
| React components | `PascalCase` file & export | `DocumentCard.tsx` |
| Classes | `PascalCase` | `AppError` |
| Functions / variables | `camelCase` | `fetchDocuments` |
| Constants | `SCREAMING_SNAKE` | `MAX_FILE_SIZE` |
| Zod schemas | `camelCase + Schema` | `uploadDocumentSchema` |
| Types/Interfaces | `PascalCase` | `Document`, `ApiResponse<T>` |

## TypeScript Rules
- `strict: true` always — no `any`, no `as unknown as X` escape hatches
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for plain data shapes; use `interface` for extensible contracts
- Explicit return types on all exported functions
- Never use non-null assertion (`!`) — use guard or throw instead

## Error Handling
- All async code wrapped in try/catch; errors forwarded to the next error handler (backend) or displayed via toast (frontend)
- Use typed `AppError` subclasses — never `throw new Error('raw string')` in business logic
- Log at the boundary (controller/page), not deep in service layers

## Feature Development Workflow
- One PR per feature slice — never mix unrelated changes
- New feature = new module in `backend/src/modules/<name>/` + `frontend/src/features/<name>/`
- Update shared types first, then backend, then frontend

## Comments & Docs
- No comments that restate what the code does
- JSDoc on all exported functions in `lib/` and `services/`
- Inline comments only for non-obvious "why", not "what"
